summary: Investing.com -- Recently confirmed Trump administration Federal Housing Finance Agency director, William Pulte, wants to make Fannie Mae (OTC:FNMA) and Freddie Mac (OTC:FMCC) great again.

headline: Privatizing Fannie and Freddie not a top priority, says Trump’s new FHFA director
summary: Bill Pulte, who was confirmed by the US Senate on Thursday to lead the Federal Housing Finance Agency for the Trump administration, said he’s in no rush to privatize Fannie Mae and Freddie Mac, the mortgage behemoths that power more than half of America’s mortgages.
